{"id": "19149", "revid": "46586549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19149", "title": "Bristleback tribe", "text": "The Bristleback tribe (or the Bristleback Quilboars) is a &lt;a href=\"tribe\"&gt;tribe&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"quilboar\"&gt;quilboar&lt;/a&gt; that inhabit &lt;a href=\"Mulgore\"&gt;Mulgore&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Barrens\"&gt;Barrens&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Bristlebacks of Brambleblade Ravine are at war with the &lt;a href=\"tauren\"&gt;tauren&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Camp%20Narache\"&gt;Camp Narache&lt;/a&gt; and they encroached on the area of &lt;a href=\"Red%20Cloud%20Mesa\"&gt;Red Cloud Mesa&lt;/a&gt;. They train &lt;a href=\"Battleboar\"&gt;Battleboar&lt;/a&gt;s to be malicious. Young tauren entered the ravine and killed the Bristleback leader &lt;a href=\"Chief%20Sharptusk%20Thornmantle\"&gt;Chief Sharptusk Thornmantle&lt;/a&gt;. The quilboar also ravaged the tauren burial site of Red Rocks.\nIn the Barrens they were at war with the &lt;a href=\"Razormane%20tribe\"&gt;Razormane&lt;/a&gt; quilboar. At the start of the &lt;a href=\"war%20against%20the%20Lich%20King\"&gt;war against the Lich King&lt;/a&gt;, Bristlebacks became more aggressive and killed a female tauren and her young son. When Hamuul Runetotem performed a ritual for the deceased in Red Rocks a few of them attacked the Archdruid.\nDuring the Cataclysm, quilboar of Mulgore were in turmoil. New High Chieftain &lt;a href=\"Baine%20Bloodhoof\"&gt;Baine Bloodhoof&lt;/a&gt; stopped the war against them allowing them to take resources from a newly-created river. Some time later, the Bristlebacks attacked the Red Cloud Mesa tauren once again.\nThe bristlebacks dig up the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Shard\"&gt;blood shards&lt;/a&gt; and use them in battles as totems for their strength and magic.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Fourth%20War\"&gt;Fourth War&lt;/a&gt;, several of them appeared on &lt;a href=\"Kul%20Tiras\"&gt;Kul Tiras&lt;/a&gt; as members of the &lt;a href=\"Bilge%20Rats\"&gt;Bilge Rats&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn the RPG.\nBristlebacks tend to be larger and stronger than most quilboar."}
