{"id": "64826", "revid": "38791128", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=64826", "title": "Scale of the Sands", "text": "The Scale of the Sands is a secretive subgroup of the &lt;a href=\"bronze%20dragonflight\"&gt;bronze dragonflight&lt;/a&gt;, led by &lt;a href=\"Soridormi\"&gt;Soridormi&lt;/a&gt;, prime mate of &lt;a href=\"Nozdormu\"&gt;Nozdormu&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Arazmodu\"&gt;Arazmodu&lt;/a&gt; is a member of this faction. Until patch 2.4 a friendly reputation with the faction was required to enter the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20of%20Mount%20Hyjal\"&gt;Battle of Mount Hyjal&lt;/a&gt;.\nReputation.\nNote: Mobs will not give rep until first wave has been cleared or if previous boss was cleared within the soft reset time; this was implemented by Blizzard to prevent reputation grinding by small groups.\nRewards.\nYou get each ring as a quest reward from &lt;a href=\"Soridormi\"&gt;Soridormi&lt;/a&gt;. You get the first from her at friendly after completing &lt;a href=\"The%20Vials%20of%20Eternity\"&gt;The Vials of Eternity&lt;/a&gt;, and you turn in your old one for a new one at each reputation level.\nDesigns.\n&lt;a href=\"Indormi\"&gt;Indormi&lt;/a&gt; will also sell &lt;a href=\"jewelcrafting\"&gt;jewelcrafting&lt;/a&gt; designs as you advance in Scale of the Sands reputation.\nNote that copies of these designs are also offered by &lt;a href=\"Shattered%20Sun%20Offensive\"&gt;Shattered Sun Offensive&lt;/a&gt; vendors. It is easier for individuals and small groups to gain reputation with The Shattered Sun Offensive, but the designs are significantly more costly."}
