{"id": "739104", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=739104", "title": "Scalecommander Azurathel", "text": "Scalecommander Azurathel is the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Obsidian%20Warders\"&gt;Obsidian Warders&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"dracthyr\"&gt;dracthyr&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nAncient times.\nAzurathel was one of the was one of the dracthyr created by &lt;a href=\"Neltharion\"&gt;Neltharion&lt;/a&gt;, who would come to select him to serve as the Scalecommander of the &lt;a href=\"Obsidian%20Warders\"&gt;Obsidian Warders&lt;/a&gt;. Neltharion fashioned the &lt;a href=\"Forbidden%20Reach\"&gt;Forbidden Reach&lt;/a&gt; as a secret training ground for the dracthyr, where at his command Azurathel would train the Obsidian Warders in their charge with defending the allies of the &lt;a href=\"black%20dragonflight\"&gt;black dragonflight&lt;/a&gt; and protecting its strongholds. In a battle with &lt;a href=\"Raszageth\"&gt;Raszageth&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Primal%20Incarnates\"&gt;Primal Incarnates&lt;/a&gt;, the titan relic that Neltharion used to control the wills of the dracthyr was destroyed. Though Raszageth was sealed away, Neltharion could no longer directly control the dracthyr without the relic and so deemed them a risk.\nAzurathel and his people were thus subsequently ordered to the creches beneath the Forbidden Reach by Neltharion, where they were sealed away by &lt;a href=\"Malygos\"&gt;Malygos&lt;/a&gt; in magical stasis and watched over by his &lt;a href=\"blue%20dragonflight\"&gt;blue dragonflight&lt;/a&gt;. They remained there, abandoned and forgotten for nearly 20,000 years, awakened from their long slumber only when the &lt;a href=\"Primalists\"&gt;Primalists&lt;/a&gt; returned to break &lt;a href=\"Raszageth\"&gt;Raszageth&lt;/a&gt; free, as an ancient, magical surge rippled through the Forbidden Reach, the dracthyr awoke, but from their long stasis their memories became a blur.\nThe Forbidden Reach.\nAs the dracthyr awakened, he found himself trapped in stasis until he was awakened by dracthyr adventures. After his awakening, he declared that they couldn't dwell on their broken memories, but had to move forward to assess and make a plan. Thus he directed the dracthyr with acquiring their gear, and healing their fellow dracthyr. As the group moved forward, they discovered &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander%20Cindrethresh\"&gt;Scalecommander Cindrethresh&lt;/a&gt; and that the blue dragon &lt;a href=\"Lapisagos\"&gt;Lapisagos&lt;/a&gt; intended to destroy them. Though Azurathel was uneasy at the task, due to believing that the dragons and dracthyr should fight side by side, Cindrethresh reassured him that as Lapisagos intended to destroy them, they had no other choice. After slaying their enemy, the dracthyr emerged from the ruins of their creche only to discover that their training grounds had become overgrown and realized that they'd been in stasis for a very, very, long time.\nUpon noticing that a crystal was outside the creche, he sent dracthyr to investigate, where they discovered that there were crystals in front of the other creches and that they were under attack. They quickly informed Azurathel, who declared that they must reach their allies. After this declaration, he and his allies were approached by &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander%20Emberthal\"&gt;Scalecommander Emberthal&lt;/a&gt; and discovered the &lt;a href=\"Adamant%20Vigil\"&gt;Adamant Vigil&lt;/a&gt; were no more. After discovering that the &lt;a href=\"Primalists\"&gt;Primalists&lt;/a&gt; had invaded the &lt;a href=\"Stormsunder%20Crater\"&gt;Stormsunder Crater&lt;/a&gt; and were keeping the &lt;a href=\"Ebon%20Scales\"&gt;Ebon Scales&lt;/a&gt; trapped at their creche, Emberthal sent Azurathel, &lt;a href=\"Dervishian\"&gt;Dervishian&lt;/a&gt;, and the adventurer to provide them aid. As the group headed out to rescue their allies, Azurathel directed his allies in thinning the numbers of the &lt;a href=\"Tarasek\"&gt;Tarasek&lt;/a&gt;, who had joined the Primalists, and destroy the elementals summoned by the Primalists. With their tasks complete, the trio were able to reach the Ebon Scales, where the dracthyr united and destroyed &lt;a href=\"Ekrazathal\"&gt;Ekrazathal&lt;/a&gt;. After this, &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander%20Sarkareth\"&gt;Scalecommander Sarkareth&lt;/a&gt;, demanded answers from Azurathel who told him that they would have to wait as they had to stop the Primalists.\nThe entire dracthyr army then gathered together as one and was soon joined by &lt;a href=\"Ebyssian\"&gt;Ebyssian&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wrathion\"&gt;Wrathion&lt;/a&gt;. The dracthyr and dragons then rallied to the &lt;a href=\"Froststone%20Vault\"&gt;Froststone Vault&lt;/a&gt; in order to prevent the Primalist from freeing the Raszageth, an effort they would ultimately fail at. The group was forced to flee from Raszageth's fury, rallying to the safety of the ruins of the combined &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Talons\"&gt;Dark Talons&lt;/a&gt; and Obsidian Warders creche. It was there that they were joined by &lt;a href=\"Nozdormu\"&gt;Nozdormu&lt;/a&gt;, who declared that the kingdoms of &lt;a href=\"Azeroth\"&gt;Azeroth&lt;/a&gt; had to be warned of Raszageth's release. Thus, Azurathel and the Obsidian Waders decided to join with Wrathion, who would guide them to the &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt;. Before they departed, Azurathel requested that Sarkareth and his Ebon Scales joined them; however, Sarkareth refused, renamed his group the Sundered Flame, and declared that they would claim their destiny by right. As he watched them depart, Azurathel reflected that their anger sent them down a dark path and feared the day he would meet Sarkareth as a rival on the field of battle. As they neared &lt;a href=\"Stormwind%20City\"&gt;Stormwind City&lt;/a&gt;, he was impressed with its walls and declared that it would hold strong against a formidable adversary. As the dracthyr neared the city gates, they were approached by hostile guards. However, &lt;a href=\"Mathias%20Shaw\"&gt;Mathias Shaw&lt;/a&gt; soon arrived and after a brief exchange allowed the group to enter the city. He and Wrathion then presented the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Aspects\"&gt;Dragon Aspects&lt;/a&gt; invitation to visit the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Isles\"&gt;Dragon Isles&lt;/a&gt;.\nDragonflight.\nAzurathel and Wrathion then met with &lt;a href=\"Turalyon\"&gt;Turalyon&lt;/a&gt;, where Wrathion declared that &lt;a href=\"Alexstrasza\"&gt;Alexstrasza&lt;/a&gt; would be pleased that the Alliance had answered the call but would insist that conflict is not brought to their shores. Azurathel reminded them that the isles were home to the dracthyr as well and not a place to plunder. He then declared their intention to accompany the Alliance on their journey, while reflecting that it would take time to build trust between them. Turalyon admitted that as a fellow soldier, he perfectly understood his wariness.\nHe directed adventurers with delivering his orders to his &lt;a href=\"lieutenant\"&gt;lieutenant&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dervishian\"&gt;Dervishian&lt;/a&gt;. As Azurathel and his Obsidian Warders arrived at the &lt;a href=\"Stormwind%20Harbor\"&gt;Stormwind Harbor&lt;/a&gt;, they were joined by Emberthal, who shared that Nozdormu had revealed to her the origins of the dracthyr, how Neltharion had put them to sleep, and that they had been in stasis for nearly twenty thousand years.\nQuotes.\nGossip.\nHe and &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander%20Cindrethresh\"&gt;Scalecommander Cindrethresh&lt;/a&gt; have a \"voiced\" conversation in &lt;a href=\"Weyrnrest\"&gt;Weyrnrest&lt;/a&gt;:\nNow that the storms have passed, we've got Primalists searching the island, pirates and rivals trying to grab all they can, and rebel dracthyr trying to force us off the island.\nLook, I appreciate that everyone needs a place to sleep and food to eat, but first, we need to make sure no one's going to get killed. We've got a job to do. It's time to fight."}
{"id": "739103", "revid": "38791128", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=739103", "title": "Scalecommander Cindrethresh", "text": "Scalecommander Cindrethresh is the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Talons\"&gt;Dark Talons&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"dracthyr\"&gt;dracthyr&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nAncient times.\nCindrethresh was one of the dracthyr created by &lt;a href=\"Neltharion\"&gt;Neltharion&lt;/a&gt;, who would come to select her to serve as the Scalecommander of the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Talons\"&gt;Dark Talons&lt;/a&gt;. Neltharion fashioned the &lt;a href=\"Forbidden%20Reach\"&gt;Forbidden Reach&lt;/a&gt; as a secret training ground for the dracthyr, where at his command Cindrethresh would train the Dark Talons to be an elite force would be feared by all enemies of the &lt;a href=\"black%20dragonflight\"&gt;black dragonflight&lt;/a&gt;. In a battle with &lt;a href=\"Raszageth\"&gt;Raszageth&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Primal%20Incarnates\"&gt;Primal Incarnates&lt;/a&gt;, the titan relic that Neltharion used to control the wills of the dracthyr was destroyed. Though Raszageth was sealed away, Neltharion could no longer directly control the dracthyr without the relic and so deemed them a risk.\nCindrethresh and her people were thus subsequently ordered to the creches beneath the Forbidden Reach by Neltharion, where they were sealed away by &lt;a href=\"Malygos\"&gt;Malygos&lt;/a&gt; in magical stasis and watched over by his &lt;a href=\"blue%20dragonflight\"&gt;blue dragonflight&lt;/a&gt;. They remained there, abandoned and forgotten for nearly 20,000 years, awakened from their long slumber only when the &lt;a href=\"Primalists\"&gt;Primalists&lt;/a&gt; returned to break &lt;a href=\"Raszageth\"&gt;Raszageth&lt;/a&gt; free, as an ancient, magical surge rippled through the Forbidden Reach, the dracthyr awoke, but from their long stasis their memories became a blur.\nThe Forbidden Reach.\nAs the dracthyr awakened, &lt;a href=\"Lapisagos\"&gt;Lapisagos&lt;/a&gt; ordered the blues to destroy them, a fact which took the awakened Cindrethresh off guard. She was soon approached by a group of dracthyr led by &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander%20Azurathel\"&gt;Scalecommander Azurathel&lt;/a&gt;, which gave her the reinforcements she needed to combat Lapisagos. Though Azurathel was uneasy at the task, due to believing that the dragons and dracthyr should fight side by side, Cindrethresh reassured him that as Lapisagos intended to destroy them, they had no other choice. After slaying their enemy, the dracthyr emerged from the ruins of their creche only to discover that their training grounds had become overgrown and realized that they'd been in stasis for a very, very, long time.\nAfter helping &lt;a href=\"Dracthyr%20%28playable%29\"&gt;other&lt;/a&gt; awakened dracthyr practice their abilities, she and her allies were approached by &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander%20Emberthal\"&gt;Scalecommander Emberthal&lt;/a&gt; and discovered the &lt;a href=\"Adamant%20Vigil\"&gt;Adamant Vigil&lt;/a&gt; were no more. Determined not to lose any more of their people, Emberthal directed Cindrethresh to lead dracthyr adventurers to the &lt;a href=\"Caldera%20of%20the%20Menders\"&gt;Caldera of the Menders&lt;/a&gt; in order check on, and if need be rescue on the &lt;a href=\"Healing%20Wings\"&gt;Healing Wings&lt;/a&gt;. As they flew towards the area, it was revealed that Cindrethresh was rather close with &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander%20Viridia\"&gt;Scalecommander Viridia&lt;/a&gt;. Upon their arrival they were stunned to discover wounded members of the weyrn outside and that the creche itself had been overrun with bugs and toxic fumes. The pair then rushed into the creche in order to save anyone inside, only to fall victim to the fumes themselves, and ended up being saved by Viridia. While she remained behind to look after Viridia, she directed adventurers to thinning out the &lt;a href=\"scythid\"&gt;scythid&lt;/a&gt; in the area to ensure the safety of the dracthyr. After the Healing Winds were successfully saved and restored, she remained to help while the adventurers went on ahead.\nAfter &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander%20Sarkareth\"&gt;Scalecommander Sarkareth&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Ebon%20Scales\"&gt;Ebon Scales&lt;/a&gt; were rescued, the entire dracthyr army gathered together as one and were soon joined by &lt;a href=\"Ebyssian\"&gt;Ebyssian&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wrathion\"&gt;Wrathion&lt;/a&gt;. The dracthyr and dragons then rallied to the &lt;a href=\"Froststone%20Vault\"&gt;Froststone Vault&lt;/a&gt; in order to prevent the Primalist from freeing the Raszageth, an effort they would ultimately fail at. The group was forced to flee from Raszageth's fury, rallying to the safety of the ruins of the combined Dark Talons and &lt;a href=\"Obsidian%20Warders\"&gt;Obsidian Warders&lt;/a&gt; creche. It was there that they were joined by &lt;a href=\"Nozdormu\"&gt;Nozdormu&lt;/a&gt;, who declared that the kingdoms of &lt;a href=\"Azeroth\"&gt;Azeroth&lt;/a&gt; must be warned of Raszageth's release. Thus Cindrethresh and her Dark Talons decided to join with Ebyssian, who would guide them to the &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt;. Before they departed, she requested that Viridia and the Healing Wings join them, however Viridia refused and declared that she would go to the mainland of the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Isles\"&gt;Dragon Isles&lt;/a&gt; in order to help those in need. As they arrived to &lt;a href=\"Orgrimmar\"&gt;Orgrimmar&lt;/a&gt;, she was impressed by its structure but confident that it would not be able to keep them out. As they neared the city gates, they were met by hostile guards. However &lt;a href=\"Mayla%20Highmountain\"&gt;Mayla Highmountain&lt;/a&gt; soon arrived and diffused the situation. She then guided Ebyssian and Cindrethresh to the &lt;a href=\"Horde%20Council\"&gt;Horde Council&lt;/a&gt;, where the Ebyssian presented the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Aspects\"&gt;Dragon Aspects&lt;/a&gt; invitation to visit the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Isles\"&gt;Dragon Isles&lt;/a&gt;. \nDragonflight.\nCindrethresh, Ebyssian, Mayla, and &lt;a href=\"Baine%20Bloodhoof\"&gt;Baine Bloodhoof&lt;/a&gt; met together soon after, where Ebyssian explained how the isles held great wonder and many perils and that &lt;a href=\"Alexstrasza\"&gt;Alexstrasza&lt;/a&gt; would not abide conflict on their shores. Cindrethresh reminded that the isles were home to the dracthyr as well and that they intended to rediscover their past and lay claim to their future. She and Dark Talons were then formally invited into the Horde, to which the dracthyr accepted.\nAfter the creation of the &lt;a href=\"Dragonscale%20Expedition\"&gt;Dragonscale Expedition&lt;/a&gt;, Cindrethresh declared the Dark Talons would serve as their protection detail. While she discussed the mission logistics with Ebyssian and the Horde council, she directed adventurers with delivering her orders to her &lt;a href=\"lieutenant\"&gt;lieutenant&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Kodethi\"&gt;Kodethi&lt;/a&gt;. As Cindrethresh and her Dark Talons arrived at the &lt;a href=\"zeppelin%20tower\"&gt;zeppelin tower&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Dranosh%27ar%20Blockade\"&gt;Dranosh'ar Blockade&lt;/a&gt; near the port, they were joined by Emberthal, who shared that Nozdormu had revealed to her the origins of the dracthyr, how Neltharion had put them to sleep, and that they had been in stasis for nearly twenty thousand years.\nAfter arriving to the &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Coast\"&gt;Wild Coast&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Waking%20Shores\"&gt;Waking Shores&lt;/a&gt;, she directed adventures with culling the numbers of the &lt;a href=\"Primal%20Proto-Drake\"&gt;Primal Proto-Drake&lt;/a&gt; in order to ensure that the expedition couldn't be ended before it truly began. As adventures departed to carry out their tasks, &lt;a href=\"Naleidea%20Rivergleam\"&gt;Naleidea Rivergleam&lt;/a&gt; directed the group with moving towards the &lt;a href=\"Wingrest%20Embassy\"&gt;Wingrest Embassy&lt;/a&gt; in order to meet with &lt;a href=\"Wrathion\"&gt;Wrathion&lt;/a&gt;. As they moved forward Cindrethresh, wanting a good fight, hoped the embassy was under attack. However her hopes for a fight were dashed and when adventures returned to her, she warned them that it was \"eat or be eaten in the Dragon Isles.\"\nSometime later, Cindrethresh made the journey to &lt;a href=\"Valdrakken\"&gt;Valdrakken&lt;/a&gt;, where she reunited with &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander%20Azurathel\"&gt;Azurathel&lt;/a&gt;, remarked that &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander%20Sarkareth\"&gt;Sarkareth&lt;/a&gt;'s absence was probably a good thing as he would most likely cause an incident, and expressed her desire to find where &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander%20Viridia\"&gt;Viridia&lt;/a&gt; went. When questioned as to how she was adapting to the world, she admitted that she loved how the Horde turned out to be a collection of undisciplined misfits and outcasts all held together with a loose desire to be better people and honor, and found her &lt;a href=\"visage\"&gt;visage&lt;/a&gt; to be magical. She further reflected that Neltharion had earned his title as &lt;a href=\"Deathwing\"&gt;Deathwing&lt;/a&gt; and was terrified of what he might have asked them to do had he used them in the field.\nSome time after the death of &lt;a href=\"Raszageth\"&gt;Raszageth&lt;/a&gt;, Cindrethresh and her fellow dracthyr returned to the &lt;a href=\"Forbidden%20Reach\"&gt;Forbidden Reach&lt;/a&gt;. As part of the campaign to reclaim the area, she directed adventurers with striking various enemies within the isles, while also accepting gathered information from her Horde allies.\nQuotes.\nGossip.\n He and &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander%20Azurathel\"&gt;Scalecommander Azurathel&lt;/a&gt; have a \"voiced\" conversation in &lt;a href=\"Weyrnrest\"&gt;Weyrnrest&lt;/a&gt;:\nI'm worried about Viridia. She works so hard. She takes on so much, worrying about everyone's welfare.\nI know she's a strong leader, but if she seems a little overworked... could you let me know?"}
{"id": "740206", "revid": "46586549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=740206", "title": "Scalecommander Emberthal", "text": "Scalecommander Emberthal is one of the five Scalecommanders of the &lt;a href=\"dracthyr\"&gt;dracthyr&lt;/a&gt;. She led the &lt;a href=\"Adamant%20Vigil\"&gt;Adamant Vigil&lt;/a&gt; and serves as the main neutral dracthyr that players interact with.\nBiography.\nAncient past.\nEmberthal, and all dracthyr, were created by &lt;a href=\"Neltharion\"&gt;Neltharion&lt;/a&gt; the Earth-Warder, &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Aspect\"&gt;Dragon Aspect&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"black%20dragonflight\"&gt;black dragonflight&lt;/a&gt;, as the ultimate soldiers. After a battle against &lt;a href=\"Raszageth\"&gt;Raszageth&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Primal%20Incarnates\"&gt;Primal Incarnates&lt;/a&gt;, the dracthyr were put into a magical stasis by the &lt;a href=\"blue%20dragonflight\"&gt;blue dragonflight&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Forbidden%20Reach\"&gt;Forbidden Reach&lt;/a&gt;.\nDragonflight.\nForbidden Reach.\n20,000 years later, the dracthyr including Emberthal awoke when the &lt;a href=\"Primalists\"&gt;Primalists&lt;/a&gt; attacked the Forbidden Reach to free &lt;a href=\"Raszageth\"&gt;Raszageth&lt;/a&gt;. Because of their long slumber, they could remember little besides that Neltharion was their creator. Emberthal was the only survivor of her weyrn, the rest of the &lt;a href=\"Adamant%20Vigil\"&gt;Adamant Vigil&lt;/a&gt; having died in the attack.\nLegacies.\nEmberthal encounters &lt;a href=\"Nozdormu\"&gt;Nozdormu&lt;/a&gt;, who helps her with her amnesia by informing her about the history of dragonkind. She is shocked to learn that her own creator, Neltharion, turned against his own kind and became Deathwing, having been corrupted by the whispers of the &lt;a href=\"Old%20God\"&gt;Old God&lt;/a&gt;s. Even further still when she learned that after the defeat of Raszageth, Neltharion sealed the dracthyr away and essentially forgot about them.\nDragon Isles.\nAs the &lt;a href=\"Dragonscale%20Expedition\"&gt;Dragonscale Expedition&lt;/a&gt; prepares to leave for the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Isles\"&gt;Dragon Isles&lt;/a&gt;, Emberthal travels to &lt;a href=\"Stormwind\"&gt;Stormwind&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Orgrimmar\"&gt;Orgrimmar&lt;/a&gt; to inform the dracthyr there of what Nozdormu told her.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Waking%20Shores\"&gt;Waking Shores&lt;/a&gt;, Emberthal aids &lt;a href=\"Wrathion\"&gt;Wrathion&lt;/a&gt; and the black flight in retaking the &lt;a href=\"Obsidian%20Citadel\"&gt;Obsidian Citadel&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"djaradin\"&gt;djaradin&lt;/a&gt;. Afterward, she travels to the &lt;a href=\"Obsidian%20Observatory\"&gt;Obsidian Observatory&lt;/a&gt;, a place that had been of personal importance to Neltharion. While there, she and a dracthyr adventurer uncover records of Neltharion's plans to make the dracthyr to fight the Incarnates. When Emberthal sees that Neltharion had only made them as soldiers for war, she decides that is something the dracthyr must make peace with.\nSome time afterward, Emberthal heard that the blue dragonflight was in the &lt;a href=\"Azure%20Span\"&gt;Azure Span&lt;/a&gt;, and went to investigate alongside &lt;a href=\"Telash%20Greywing\"&gt;Telash Greywing&lt;/a&gt; given the dracthyr's history with the blue dragons. There they encountered &lt;a href=\"Khadgar\"&gt;Khadgar&lt;/a&gt;, who explained that he and the &lt;a href=\"Kirin%20Tor\"&gt;Kirin Tor&lt;/a&gt; were not the servants of the blue flight, but rather their friends. Khadgar was unnerved by the dracthyr saying that the blue dragons had imprisoned them, and promised to investigate. Emberthal and Telash then traveled to the &lt;a href=\"Azure%20Archives\"&gt;Azure Archives&lt;/a&gt; to learn about their captivity by &lt;a href=\"Malygos\"&gt;Malygos&lt;/a&gt;. With the help of &lt;a href=\"Sindragosa\"&gt;Sindragosa&lt;/a&gt;'s arcane simulacrum, they uncovered Malygos's journals detailing how Neltharion had been beside himself and insisted the dracthyr had needed to be contained. Telash did not take the information well and ran further into the archives, insisting that Sindragosa was lying, while Emberthal stayed behind to speak to her and read more from Malygos's library.\nReturn to the Forbidden Reach.\nFollowing the death of &lt;a href=\"Raszageth\"&gt;Raszageth&lt;/a&gt;, her storms around the &lt;a href=\"Forbidden%20Reach\"&gt;Forbidden Reach&lt;/a&gt; vanished, opening the way for the dracthyr and their allies to return. Scalecommander Emberthal, who viewed the isle as the closet thing to a home the dracthyr had, was determined to claim it and had the support of &lt;a href=\"Ebyssian\"&gt;Ebyssian&lt;/a&gt;, who tried to take on an advisory role for the Scalecommander. However, it was not a smooth partnership, with Emberthal making it clear that she was not pleased with Ebyssian's decision to hide from the rest of the world and frequently criticized Ebyssian as the pair worked together, even as he attempted to diffuse matters. With &lt;a href=\"Talon%20Damos\"&gt;Talon Damos&lt;/a&gt; as her second-in-command, and accompanied by adventurers, Emberthal lead a group of dracthyr further into Reach, while Ebyssian remained behind at &lt;a href=\"Morqut%20Village\"&gt;Morqut Village&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter reaching the &lt;a href=\"Lost%20Atheneum\"&gt;Lost Atheneum&lt;/a&gt;, Emberthal instructed her people to secure it, as she investigated the ruins for any information. She privately admitted to adventurers that after everything that happened, everything the dracthyr have been through, she questioned if what she sought wasn't there. Her musings were cut off after Damos' called out to her, and she rushed out to check on him only to discover that he and the others had been slain by &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander%20Sarkareth\"&gt;Scalecommander Sarkareth&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Sundered%20Flame\"&gt;Sundered Flame&lt;/a&gt;. Amidst her grief, Ebyssian arrived and revealed that the Sundered Flame had begun attacking members of the &lt;a href=\"Dragonscale%20Expedition\"&gt;Dragonscale Expedition&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"High%20Creche\"&gt;High Creche&lt;/a&gt;. As he offered comfort to Emberthal for her loss, she lashed out at him demanding to know how many black dragons he had lost, causing Ebyssian to remark that while he had never buried his own, he did help bury generations of the &lt;a href=\"Highmountain%20Tribe\"&gt;Highmountain Tribe&lt;/a&gt;. A surprised Emberthal then realized that they had both lost many who were close to them. As the duo fought against the Sundered Flame, Emberthal tasked adventurers with pushing the Sundered Flame back, though she took no pleasure in it feeling that every dead dracthyr was a tragedy that should have been avoided. In time, the group discovered the black dragon &lt;a href=\"Adamanthia\"&gt;Adamanthia&lt;/a&gt; trapped in stasis, and discovered that &lt;a href=\"Neltharion\"&gt;Neltharion&lt;/a&gt; was not only responsible but had used her as a means to imprison and draw the essence of the black dragonflight from the dracthyr during their imprisonment. Though desiring to free her from her torment, Ebyssian advised caution and declared that they should learn more before attempting to destroy her oubliette.\nAfter discovering that Sarkareth was at &lt;a href=\"Dragonskull%20Island\"&gt;Dragonskull Island&lt;/a&gt;, Emberthal and Ebyssian once more had a clash of views, before Emberthal headed off to the island alone. Upon reaching the isle, Emberthal recalled how the island was a dark place, full of pain and failure, and recalled the last time she had been present was before she was a &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander\"&gt;Scalecommander&lt;/a&gt;. She subsequently ventured into the cave determined to find Sarkareth, where she encountered the risen dead of failed Scalecommanders and memoirs of Neltharion, before discovering Sarkareth surrounded by his Sundered Flame. Despite her desire to bring justice to her fallen allies, Emberthal could not bring herself to slaughter the other dracthyr, and so Sarkareth was able to escape. In the face of Sarkareth calling Emberthal a coward, Ebyssian countered it wasn't weakness that stayed her hand, but the strength in her compassion, conviction, and loyalty to her people, which should be an inspiration to them all. He then approached Emberthal and questioned what she would do if she followed Sarkareth, causing her to remark that she would extinguish him as she had been trained to do by Neltharion. In response, he remarked that the enemy was one of her own, as were the dracthyr that followed him, and that like her they were soldiers who had been conditioned to claim victory at any cost. Outraged, Emberthal asked how Ebyssian could presume to know them after he hid amongst the mortals while other dragons fought and died to protect the world. Ebyssian then acknowledged that she was right; he had turned away from the world, and he was just content to be \"Ebonhorn\" with &lt;a href=\"Highmountain\"&gt;Highmountain&lt;/a&gt; as his home. He admitted that while he should have done more, his shame as Neltharion's offspring prevented that, and that he had come to the Forbidden Reach to face that, only to find her. When Emberthal declared he must be disappointed, he rejected the notion by pointing out that she had defied his voice inside of her, that she chose compassion over violence, and declared that their family doesn't have to live in his shadow. He then vowed that they would help one another, as he promised to aid Emberthal in ensuring that Sarkareth would face justice for all he had done. \nIn the aftermath, she instructed adventurers to work with &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander%20Viridia\"&gt;Scalecommander Viridia&lt;/a&gt; in building Morqut Village as a safe place for the dracthyr, the tuskarr, and their allies in the Reach.\nEmbers of Neltharion.\nAfter the &lt;a href=\"Incarnates\"&gt;Incarnates&lt;/a&gt; opened the way into the &lt;a href=\"Zaralek%20Cavern\"&gt;Zaralek Cavern&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Alexstrasza\"&gt;Alexstrasza&lt;/a&gt; called upon Ebyssian, &lt;a href=\"Sabellian\"&gt;Sabellian&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wrathion\"&gt;Wrathion&lt;/a&gt;, and the adventurer to enter and deal with &lt;a href=\"Fyrakk\"&gt;Fyrakk&lt;/a&gt;. While Sabellian and Wrathion immediately set off to the caverns, Ebyssian detoured and recruited Scalecommander Emberthal to their mission. Unwillingly to wait for Ebyssian and Emberthal to arrive, Sabellian and Wrathion ventured forth into the caverns, where they did battle with the &lt;a href=\"Primalists\"&gt;Primalists&lt;/a&gt;, lost a skirmish against Fyrakk, and made allies of the &lt;a href=\"Loamm%20Niffen\"&gt;Loamm Niffen&lt;/a&gt;. Thus when Ebyssian and Emberthal arrived, they found a safe haven in &lt;a href=\"Loamm\"&gt;Loamm&lt;/a&gt;, with Emberthal expressing her fascination at the fact an entire world existed below them. At the same time the &lt;a href=\"Black%20dragonflight\"&gt;Black dragonflight&lt;/a&gt; acknowledged that they were hearing whispers from within the caverns and Sabellian shared that he had discovered that the &lt;a href=\"Sundered%20Flame\"&gt;Sundered Flame&lt;/a&gt; were seeking a laboratory known as &lt;a href=\"Aberrus%2C%20the%20Shadowed%20Crucible\"&gt;Aberrus, the Shadowed Crucible&lt;/a&gt;, to which Emberthal realized securing it was &lt;a href=\"Scalecommander%20Sarkareth\"&gt;Scalecommander Sarkareth&lt;/a&gt; goal.\nWhile Sabellian on dealing with Fyrakk and Wrathion hunting out information about Aberrus, Emberthal found herself reinforced by Ebyssian as she ventured to &lt;a href=\"Nal%20ks%27kol\"&gt;Nal ks'kol&lt;/a&gt;, a titan facility in the southeastern portion of Zaralek. After the pair were able to enter the vault, they discovered Sarkareth and the Sundered Flame had not only entered before them, but that Sarkareth had claimed &lt;a href=\"Oathbinder\"&gt;Oathbinder&lt;/a&gt;, the artifact &lt;a href=\"Neltharion\"&gt;Neltharion&lt;/a&gt; used to control the &lt;a href=\"dracthyr\"&gt;dracthyr&lt;/a&gt;. Though Sarkareth attempted to use the artifact to enslave all his kin, he was thwarted by adventurers, and the artifact was destroyed by Emberthal. In the aftermath, an outraged Sarkareth claimed that Neltharion called to them from Aberrus, which confused both Emberthal and brought worry from Ebyssian. Though Sarkareth was able to flee, Emberthal realized that he was going to Aberrus. In the aftermath, Emberthal decided to offer &lt;a href=\"Amythora\"&gt;Amythora&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Marithos\"&gt;Marithos&lt;/a&gt;, members of the Sundered Flame abandoned by Sarkareth, the chance to move forward and away from the Sundered Flame. As both realized that they had been used and betrayed by Sarkareth, they accepted her offer.\nUpon returning to Loamm and seeing if Sabellian and Wrathion had discovered a means to stop Fyrakk, Emberthal, and Ebyssian instead found themselves being questioned by the pair as to what treasures they had found. Unimpressed with their content, he questioned what was truly important and who was the rightful heir to a legacy of deceit, control, and fear. When Sabellian and Wrathion grew outraged at the destruction of the Oathbinder, Ebyssian called them out on their bickering, declared that Emberthal had done right for her people, and encouraged them to let go of the past, as their flight needed them here and now.\nIn time Emberthal arrived at the &lt;a href=\"Brimstone%20Garrison\"&gt;Brimstone Garrison&lt;/a&gt; with the intention of stopping Sarkareth, however, he was unaware that a large force of &lt;a href=\"Drakonid\"&gt;drakonids&lt;/a&gt; still loyal to the memory of &lt;a href=\"Neltharion\"&gt;Neltharion&lt;/a&gt;, were present in Zaralek and had bent the knee to Sarkareth. Ebyssian having discovered this, sent adventurers to aid her. Emberthal welcomed their aid and fought against Sarkareth, during the fight she acknowledged that he had a right to follow the dark whispers if he desired to but requested that he not drag their people down with him, that he let them make their own choice. However, Sarkareth was unmoved and declared that Sundered Flame were his to use as he sought fit. After being beaten, Sarkareth retreated. Knowing that the time had come to assault Aberrus Ebyssian was able to rally Sabellian and the &lt;a href=\"Obsidian%20Brood\"&gt;Obsidian Brood&lt;/a&gt; and Wrathion and the &lt;a href=\"Blacktalon\"&gt;Blacktalons&lt;/a&gt; for the assault and united them with Emberthal. Thus the black dragonflight fought against Sarkareth's within the &lt;a href=\"Brimstone%20Garrison\"&gt;Brimstone Garrison&lt;/a&gt;, defeating them, and forcing Sarkareth to retreat within the safety of Aberrus.\nAs Sabellian and Wrathion rushed off to prevent Sarkareth from gaining control of the lab, Emberthal made the decision to remain behind, as she had grown weary of fighting her own kin and voiced her own surprise that Ebyssian didn't join them. After a moment of silence, Ebyssian admitted that he felt that the two had to face this without him and that he hoped in their pursuit they would come to see that Neltharion's legacy is death and nothing more. Thus Emberthal invited Ebyssian to join her in finding dracthyr who have yet succumbed to that fate.\nIn the aftermath of Sarkareth's death, Emberthal was given the shards of Sarkareth's signet, at the best of Ebyssian who believed that she would appreciate the gesture., In the end, Ebyssian proved correct, as Emberthal made the decision to treat Sarkareth's corpse with respect, with the hope that his memory would be a lesson, for others to not follow the illusion of Neltharion's legacy, and vowed that it was time for the dracthyr to make their own path. Ebyssian then questioned where she hoped it would lead, causing the Scalecommander to admit that she hoped to lead far from the shadows of the past that have haunted them, to make them free to build a legacy of their own, and admitted that it was Ebyssian himself who had inspired herself to believe in such a future.\nIn turn, Sabellian and Wrathion both reflected on Neltharion's legacy as both the Earth-Warder and Deathwing, and each made the decision to step down, leaving Ebyssian to be the future Aspect and leader of the black dragonflight. Upon witnessing, Emberthal remarked that Ebyssian's days of hiding were truly over, while Ebyssian was deeply humbled and vowed that their trust and faith would guide his every step.\nFractures in Time.\nAfter Emberthal and &lt;a href=\"Ebyssian\"&gt;Ebyssian&lt;/a&gt; decided to unbind the ancient siphons that were extracting the black dragonflight essence from dracthyr and &lt;a href=\"Adamanthia\"&gt;Adamanthia&lt;/a&gt; from her imprisonment, Emberthal called upon Dracthyr adventures to aid them. However due to her long time in stasis, she lashed out against the trio only for the fighting to cease when she came to her senses. In the aftermath, Emberthal reflected on how the Dracthyr had reclaimed the black dragon essence taken from them and freed the one dragon who decided to help them over obeying Neltharion. She further expressed her hope that Adamanthia would decide to join them after she finished healing and planned on informing her of all that she missed on Azeroth during her imprisonment.\nFury Incarnate.\nWhile locating the repatriating independent bands of &lt;a href=\"dracthyr\"&gt;dracthyr&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Valdrakken\"&gt;Valdrakken&lt;/a&gt;, Emberthal learned from &lt;a href=\"Amythora\"&gt;Amythora&lt;/a&gt; that the &lt;a href=\"Sundered%20Flame\"&gt;Sundered Flame&lt;/a&gt; lived on and had captured &lt;a href=\"Marithos\"&gt;Marithos&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Lonely%20Falls\"&gt;Lonely Falls&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Azure%20Span\"&gt;Azure Span&lt;/a&gt;. After Marithos was rescued, Emberthal directed her allies to approach &lt;a href=\"Quartermaster%20Doros\"&gt;Quartermaster Doros&lt;/a&gt; in the hope that he would cease the conflict. However, Doros refused and fought to the death under the banner of the Sundered Flame. Knowing that the Sundered Flame were not going to take Doros' death well and knowing how Marithos and Amythora were vulnerable, Emberthal declared that the perimeter had to be secured and the Sundered Flame kept away from. However, the group was discovered by the Sundered Flame, but before a battle could commence &lt;a href=\"Winglord%20Dezran\"&gt;Winglord Dezran&lt;/a&gt; arrived and was able to convince the Sundered Flame that they needed to become the Ebon Scales once more, with Emberthal serving as their Scalecommander, a position she accepted, while retaining Dezran as Winglord. With the Ebon Scales reborn, the dracthyr returned to Valdrakken where Emberthal pledged to work to bring the dracthyr together.\nQuotes.\nGossip.\nI shall seek answers after I have accounted for all of the dracthyr.\nThere is so much we do not know about our past... about our future...\nI intend to change that.\nVideos.\n&lt;vplayer/&gt;"}
