{"id": "740615", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=740615", "title": "Scalecommander Viridia", "text": "Scalecommander Viridia is one of the five Scalecommanders of the &lt;a href=\"dracthyr\"&gt;dracthyr&lt;/a&gt;. She leads the &lt;a href=\"Healing%20Wings\"&gt;Healing Wings&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter the events of the dracthyr starting zone, Viridia can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Obsidian%20Enclave\"&gt;Obsidian Enclave&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Valdrakken\"&gt;Valdrakken&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuotes.\nGossip.\n&lt;Viridia is a leader who is looked up to by all of her subordinates. So much so that when she finds herself free of the military regiment and decides to go independant, her old battallion tries to follow her even though they no longer have orders to do so. They trust her judgement and will fight by her side to the end.\nAs for Viridia herself, she is a kind person Who trained healers, not soldiers. She is a combat medic used to battlefield conditions and no stranger to stress. However, she would rather heal than hurt, and prefers a life of neutrality in the wars of the the world. &gt;\nI gathered all that I could. The drakonid have decided to follow us.\nWe have been gathering supplies as we made our way here but there is not enough life on this island to support this many dracthyr. There never was.\nOur position feels very precarious here.\nWhen we leave here, we will leave behind our old ways. No more weyrns, no more dragons, no more chain of command.\nWe will be free. And that may prove to be terrifying for some of our kind.\nThis city is so... decadent.\nSince the &lt;a href=\"Forbidden%20Reach\"&gt;Forbidden Reach&lt;/a&gt; I have seen so much pain and suffering in this landscape and here stands a testament to the power of &lt;a href=\"dragon\"&gt;dragon&lt;/a&gt;s and a reminder of how little they used it to aid others before now."}
