{"id": "627710", "revid": "38791128", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=627710", "title": "Liberation of Kezan", "text": "The Liberation of Kezan happened 100 years before the opening of the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Portal\"&gt;Dark Portal&lt;/a&gt; when the &lt;a href=\"goblin\"&gt;goblin&lt;/a&gt; slaves to &lt;a href=\"Zandalari%20troll\"&gt;Zandalari troll&lt;/a&gt;s on the island of &lt;a href=\"Kezan\"&gt;Kezan&lt;/a&gt; rose up against their troll overseers armed with technology beyond what the Zandalari possessed. The revolution shattered the trolls' hold over Kezan and the surviving Zandalari fled.\nAftermath.\nThe goblins celebrated their new liberation by turning on each other in a mad scramble to fill the void of power. Amid the chaos as countless factions and allegiances formed. The most powerful of these groups were known as &lt;a href=\"Cartel\"&gt;cartels&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlthough they no longer inhabit it, Kezan is still sacred to the Zandalari to this day.\nSpeculation.\nThe conflict that emerged between the goblins is possibly the first of the &lt;a href=\"Trade%20Wars\"&gt;Trade Wars&lt;/a&gt;."}
