{"id": "21911", "revid": "46586549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21911", "title": "Ur", "text": "Ur was a &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Dalaran\"&gt;Dalaran&lt;/a&gt; before the coming of the &lt;a href=\"Scourge\"&gt;Scourge&lt;/a&gt;. He was best known for his studies on &lt;a href=\"shadow%20magic\"&gt;shadow magic&lt;/a&gt; and his research on other &lt;a href=\"world\"&gt;world&lt;/a&gt;s. He is most well known for his research on the alien creatures known as &lt;a href=\"worgen\"&gt;worgen&lt;/a&gt;. Though his knowledge was great, some believed that his conscience held him from true power. He died during the &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20Dalaran\"&gt;Siege of Dalaran&lt;/a&gt; at the hands of the &lt;a href=\"Scourge\"&gt;Scourge&lt;/a&gt;.\nOne of his books, &lt;a href=\"The%20Book%20of%20Ur\"&gt;The Book of Ur&lt;/a&gt;, was held in &lt;a href=\"Shadowfang%20Keep\"&gt;Shadowfang Keep&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Archmage%20Arugal\"&gt;Archmage Arugal&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe dark mage, &lt;a href=\"Morganth\"&gt;Morganth&lt;/a&gt; also possessed a book written by Ur, &lt;a href=\"Ur%27s%20Treatise%20on%20Shadow%20Magic\"&gt;Ur's Treatise on Shadow Magic&lt;/a&gt;, which the mages of &lt;a href=\"Stormwind%20City\"&gt;Stormwind City&lt;/a&gt; wanted returned to them because they feared that Morganth might find a way to open it and read its contents."}
