{"id": "159532", "revid": "3154973", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=159532", "title": "Urn of King Terenas", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nThe Urn of King Terenas was a magical urn which contained the ashes of &lt;a href=\"King%20Terenas\"&gt;King Terenas&lt;/a&gt;. After being claimed by the &lt;a href=\"Scourge\"&gt;Scourge&lt;/a&gt;, it was instead used to store the remains of &lt;a href=\"Kel%27Thuzad\"&gt;Kel'Thuzad&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nAs part of a plot to summon the &lt;a href=\"demon%20lord\"&gt;demon lord&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Archimonde\"&gt;Archimonde&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"dreadlord\"&gt;dreadlord&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Tichondrius\"&gt;Tichondrius&lt;/a&gt; ordered the &lt;a href=\"death%20knight\"&gt;death knight&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Arthas\"&gt;Arthas&lt;/a&gt; to revive the &lt;a href=\"necromancer\"&gt;necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Kel%27Thuzad\"&gt;Kel'Thuzad&lt;/a&gt;. However, a being of Kel'Thuzad's power could only be reanimated using the energies of the &lt;a href=\"Sunwell\"&gt;Sunwell&lt;/a&gt;, and Kel'Thuzad's remains were too badly decomposed to survive a journey to &lt;a href=\"Quel%27Thalas\"&gt;Quel'Thalas&lt;/a&gt;. Tichondrius therefore charged Arthas with stealing an enchanted urn from the &lt;a href=\"Knights%20of%20the%20Silver%20Hand\"&gt;Knights of the Silver Hand&lt;/a&gt;, in which the remains could be stored and protected. After killing &lt;a href=\"Uther%20the%20Lightbringer\"&gt;Uther the Lightbringer&lt;/a&gt;, Arthas dumped his father's ashes out of the urn, then had Kel'Thuzad's remains placed inside it.\nAfter defeating the &lt;a href=\"High%20elf\"&gt;high elves&lt;/a&gt;, Arthas poured the necromancer's remains into the Sunwell, defiling it and allowing Kel'Thuzad to be reborn as an &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"lich\"&gt;lich&lt;/a&gt;.\nItem description.\n\"Ground description:\" This urn contains the remains of King Terenas.\n\"Inventory description:\" Formerly the container of King Terenas' ashes, this magically enchanted Urn was chosen by Tichondrius to preserved Kel'Thuzad's remains.\nSource.\nThis item appears after &lt;a href=\"Arthas%20%28death%20knight%29\"&gt;Arthas&lt;/a&gt; kills &lt;a href=\"Uther%20%28Warcraft%20III%29\"&gt;Uther&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Digging%20up%20the%20Dead%20%28WC3%20Undead%29\"&gt;Digging up the Dead&lt;/a&gt;, the second chapter of the \"\" undead campaign &lt;a href=\"Path%20of%20the%20Damned\"&gt;Path of the Damned&lt;/a&gt;."}
